OL,3,GUK long range forecast
OL,4,
OL,5,COutlook for Wed 22 Apr to Fri 1 May
OL,6,FHigh pressure is likely to remain
OL,7,Fcentred to the north or northwest of
OL,8,Fthe UK for much of this period amid
OL,9,Fslowly evolving weather patterns. This
OL,10,Fmeans overall, a fair amount of dry
OL,11,Fweather is expected though there will
OL,12,Flikely be some exceptions. Firstly,
OL,13,FAtlantic frontal zones may graze over
OL,14,Fthe southwest near the start of this
OL,15,Fperiod, bringing some rain and breezy
OL,16,Fconditions. The latter part of April
OL,17,Fmay also see cold air sweep south
OL,18,Facross much or all of the UK for a
OL,19,Ftime, bringing potential for wintry
OL,20,Fshowers in the north and east and more
OL,21,Fwidespread overnight frost. Any cold
OL,22,Fspell looks fairly likely to be short-
OL,23,QppppppppppppppppppppGSource: Met Office
OL,23,Flived before somewhat milder
OL,24,ANext Page  BWeather  CReg News  FReg TV
OL,24,Fconditions become re-established.
